==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Symphytism
<hw>Sym"phy*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ grown
together.]</ety> <def>Coalescence; a growing into one with another
word.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some of the phrasal adverbs have assumed the form of single words,
by that <qex>symphytism</qex> which naturally attaches these light
elements to each other.</q> <rj><qau>Earle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sympiesometer</ent>⟦br⟧
